{"build_type":"executable","description":"Rename one whole package across the entire graph in a single operation, for the §10 mass rename. Reads {old, new, roots} from stdin (old = current package name, new = the §10 name, roots = package root dirs). Steps: enumerate the universe and collect all package paths; find the old package's single function key; rename that function symbol AND every call site across all packages via the proven ed_all_packages machinery (g_rename_match/g_rename_to); rewrite the old package's package_name and module_name fields to new; then rename the directory and the .ipm file (rename syscall 82). The function key, package_name, module_name, dir, and file all become the one new hyphenated name (unify on hyphen). Manifest target/entry for build artifacts are fixed in a separate pass. Emits {status, renamed, to}. Reuses read_all_of_stdin, decode_entire_source_building_document, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, enumerate_universe_packages, count_members_inside_container_value, begin_empty_sequence_document_value, collect_universe_paths_into_array, find_package_doc_by_package_name, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, cJSON_CreateTrue, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, ed_all_packages, fetch_member_residing_within_sequence, build_store_path, create_empty_string_buffer, append_cstring_into_string_buffer, rewrite_package_name_fields_in_file, add_str_field, emit_result_object_onto_standard_output.","module_name":"rename-package-across-dependency-graph","package_name":"rename-package-across-dependency-graph","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_rename_match","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_rename_to","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"rename-package-across-dependency-graph":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","var